I need to calculate the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period (2024-01-28).

The Quick Ratio is calculated as:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

Let's extract the relevant values from the balance sheet:

1. Current Assets (as of 2024-01-28): $9,963,057.95
2. Inventory (as of 2024-01-28): $720,000.00
3. Current Liabilities (as of 2024-01-28): $829,755.77

Now I can calculate the Quick Ratio:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
Quick Ratio = ($9,963,057.95 - $720,000.00) / $829,755.77
Quick Ratio = $9,243,057.95 / $829,755.77
Quick Ratio = 11.14

Rounding to 2 decimal places: 11.14

```json
{"solution": {'Quick Ratio': '11.14'}}
```
